Intraclass correlation coefficient (ICC)2,123, confidence interval (95% IC), standard error of measurement (SEM) and minimum detectable change (MDC), coefficient of variation (CV) and Bland–Altman plots (mean difference [bias] and 95% limits of agreement[upper and lower]) were used for the analysis of the intra- and inter-examiner reliability of the HRV variables. The results from the ICC2,1 analysis were interpreted according to the Fleiss study: values below 0.40, reliability was considered low; between 0.40 and 0.75, moderate; between 0.75 and 0.90, substantial; and finally, for values greater than 0.90, reliability was rated as excellent. SEM was calculated using the formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
